Merlin.Description: Even if  you only get 2-3 spellboost this card is great. Kills a threat and sets up 2 + cards in ur hand to do more.

Witchbolt.Description: Solid removal in the 3 slot and gets a free cycle with an easyish condition. No need to spellboost this too solid.

Alchemist's Lore.Description: Lets you trade into things very easy. Dictates your midgame turns if you have it in hand for an easy reset button while saving ur evo's and the topdeck comeback card of the craft.

Arch Summoner.Description: Comes in a little slow sometimes when it's too late but in a relatively even game this card swings it in your favour a lot after his first trade/ping.

Timeworn Mage Levi.Description: This thing is a 2 for 1 card as a 2 drop. Vanilla without much but can be used on ur 4/5 to crash into something and use the 3 damage ping on anything else. Really flexible card on evolve and solid vanilla stats.

Remi/Rami.Description: You should probably force earthrite early game drops if you see this card. It's better than Floral fencer in a sense that it protects itself on board. It's as good as your earthrite synergies otherwise just a goliath. Not that many new sigils though so pretty reliant on base set ones(most are decent cards on their own)

First Curse.Description: A very exciting pile to have this one in it as there are a fair amount of janky rares in Rune. If you land this in a midrange game you have a lot of value generate from this one/three cards.

Juno's Secret Laboratory.Description: Great value over ur turns and keeps you alive to recieve it. Turns into twin guardians kinda with your earth synergy that you might have.

Calamitous Curse.Description: You actually have a pretty good board wipe in uncommon in alchemist lore and this hit's the same things most of the time. Earthrite is a tad hard to pull off at times and this thing sometimes misses important stuff or forces you into bad trades. Still Aoe is a premium and does a decent job.

Wind Blast.Description: Value enough as a 2-3 damage spell and can reach huge numbers in theory but not too reliable to charge it up.

Runic Guardian.Description: Good statline and gets bigger with a fair amount of work. Ward is good to have late where it's most likely to have a sigil.

Spectral Wizard.Description: Great stats like the above and a very solid evolve but only if you have enough spellboosts.

Petrification.Description: Poly/removal effect that takes care of problem cards or shrinks them. Bonus for earth rite.

Price of Magic.Description: Wannabe Haven card that is in rune. Finishes off things that evo trade into ur stuff quite consistantly and enables ur earthrite "for free"

Demonflame Mage.Description: Not as shiny as the other craft 4 drops but can finish off a weenie and trade into something just the same.

Lightning shooter.Description: This gets big pretty fast and helps finish off evolved units that trade into ur dudes without blowing one of ur's or another card.

Winter Caprice.Description: "Kills" a board of 2+ evo things that snowballed too much by rolling them into snowmen.

Red-Hot Ritual.Description: Slower 2 damage than dragons but u get a sigil stapled on for free. Nice payoff to enable a couple of your earthrite vanilla's. Expect this to be one of the prime things to look for when drafting remi's.

Grand Gargoyle.Description: Solid vanilla stat with added earthrite synergies. You will take this as one of your better 5 drops on average. Since your 5 pool is pretty weak this gets a nod.

Gem Golem.Description: Not really relavent ability sometimes but good statline and ward's up in the mid to late game which is good where ur usually scrambling to not die.

Gauntleted Healer.Description: The line of text is relavent healing for 2 or 3 + if ur fortunate enough and it's a solid body for trades.

Flame Witch.Description: Much better stats than above and the upside is potentially gamewinning.

Fates Hand.Description: This card is good at 3 and better as it goes on. Drafthing the spellbased deck tends to be a good way to go and this card digs u deeper.

Sun Oracle Pascal.Description: Good statline crazy effect but rune's follower quality + neutrals is pretty bad. Earthrite synergies is pretty inconsistant in arena. Still another goodstuff follower that rune gets to draft.... at legendary. You also have a much 'better' card at uncommon to use ur rare earthrites on.

Rimewind.Description: This gets to 5 in a decent spell deck and is 2 cards in one. Average to good in rune's rare slot but more of a tempo play card. Still can cause blow outs if your card quality is on par.

Penguin Wizard.Description: Vanilla with some decent upside for trading in a spell deck that but isn't too unreliable to boost to 3 or 4.

Fissure Bomb.Description: A lot of other crafts get better removal for cheaper but this tends to kill almost everything you face in the early to mid portions of the game. Ignore the bonus on this one.

Alchemist's Workshop.Description: Not too much sacrifice to a free earth sigil. Ward is a great keyword for the craft to survive and fling spells.

Conjure golem.Description: You'll probably have some ammount of spellboost hopefully that benefits from him.

Insight.Description: Best card turn 1 most of the time with enough spell boost. Great lategame as the mana isn too important and it cycles.

Apprentice Alchemist.Description: It's a free line of text which gives you free value. Strong when it activates and average when it doesn't.

Kaleidoscopic Glow.Description: Tempo bounce that doesn't set you back but less useful later. Decent filler to the curve and deck.

Summon Snow.Description: Scales off spells ofc but should to be nice even at 3-4. Not too exciting if your drafting a lot of follower or earthrite stuff.

Queen Medb.Description: Treat this like your lightning behemoths and golbin dudes that have heavy drawbacks. Sometimes helps u and sometimes hurts u a ton.

Fire Chain.Description: These kinda cards tend to be really good if you can reach a high number i hear ¯\_(ツ)_/¯.

Witchcrafter Magisa.Description: You don't give up too much for a potential win condition in a spell heavy deck. Solid filler for when you want that sorta deck.

Fiery Embrace.Description: The more spelly ur deck is the better.

Ancient Alchemist.Description: Depending on how early you get this with like 5+ things that make an earth sigil early this ranges from great to bad.

Veteran Alchemist.Description: Really nice toughness and a massive heal if u get it off. Most value it has is trading into stuff and being large enough to annoy the board while dodging small pings.

Conjure Twosome.Description: Is there gonna be a threesome one later ( ͡° ͜ʖ ͡°). Joke aside it's decent filler that fills ur board and tends to be a great trade card early like swords couragous knight.

Spurned Witch.Description: If the ping is relavent it's very good. If the stats were switched it be a lot juicier but still a decent pick.

Twin Guardians.Description: It's 6/6 worth of stats and the bonus is pretty nice if you get it without too much hassle. Good for when you are outvalueing the opponent, evolves are gone and they start going to the rush plan.

Crafty Warlock.Description: Barely under curve and doesnt matter much early minus pings and has a relavent sigil drop when it dies more often than not.

Magic Missile.Description: Good filler that is really nice late and early when you need pings.

Master Alchemist.Description: It's a fatty stated for when it doesn't trigger and that's fine to draft if you need one or more.

Crystal Bomba.Description: Just a goliath most of the time but another card for rune's lacking follower pool.

Scholary Witch.Description: He's actually pretty close to merlin without the spellboost fluff and specific search and can put you ahead of cards while trading him away.

Crest Wizard.Description: Filler that has a decent immunity effect. Evo trades also work out nice since they can't burn small removal pings on it after.

Rune Blade Summoner.Description: It doesn't have to grow too much to be good but threatens ur 4 drop since it will rot in hand a lot. Still a solid filler if you get enough spells but barely since it's draw reliant.

Scrap Iron Smelter.Description: Puts 2 'things' on the board but doesn't really do much unless you make use of the sigil with enough synergies. Actually a 0/2 ward whice is like a ding dong draw a commence. Don't take too many but 2 is pretty good with rem rins.

Sammy, Wizard's Apprentice.Description: Good and bad card advantage depending on the craft ur facing but important for curving out.

Teachings of Creation.Description: At least this one cycles to leave something semi-useless behind.

Sorcery Cache.Description: Potential to combo with other spellboosts but not consistant without a ton and is a do nothing card on it's own + pretty costly lategame for a cycle.

Elementary Academy.Description: 2's and 3's usually don't matter as much switching spots minus 2/3's and this one gives you a 2 drop + a 1 drop sigil if u wanna think of it that way.

Whirlwind mage.Description: You pick this as a 4/4 and expect it to be a 6/6 that crashes into things most of the time. Which is fine if u need a 5 drop.

Dragonbond Mage.Description: A comboey card but doesn't let you drop it on 7 and trades poorly itself while forcing you to have/hold an 'action' spell in hand.

Shadow Witch.Description: More vanilla goodness for rune. The earthrite isn't even as impactful some of the time and it's base stats aren't amazing but fair. Still free effect on a late game filler.

Multipart Experiment.Description: Bad as summon snow but much less flexible but costs so much and you need to play a couple spells with this clogging had.

Witchette Emmylou.Description: Unexciting 3 drop that gets lower like your 10 drop. Doesn't have insane stats and discounting it by 1 isn't even achieving much. You have to play this fairly on curve most of the time and even holding it to be a 1 or 0 isn't perticularly powerful.

Golem Protection.Description: I think you need a constructed level earth rite package before this is anywhere near decent. Still filler if that pile has a good pick.

Summon Iceform.Description: Does some cute things in evolve turns and can act as a end combat effect early but puts you down a card in arena to 'do nothing' which is quite bad. Has some uses but nothing your drafting towards most of the time.

Commence Experiment.Description: Can consider this a do nothing card that has some applications if you manage to draft enough earth sigil synergies but not worth a filler slot.

Arcane Enlightenment.Description: Bleh. Get 20 spell.dek with 2 merlin maybe?

Secrets of Erasmus.Description: Arch summoner for 9 is still great, and the base is excellent as well

Daria, Dimensional Witch.Description: Great given that Rune can easily make it into the later game with their array of removal spells

Anne, Belle of Mysteria.Description: I would say this is better than alexander

Dwarf Alchemist.Description: I almost always play earth rite style, so this is a godsend

Rite of Exorcism.Description: There are better removals in rune, but the flexibility makes it decent

Disaster Witch.Description: This is tough to evaluate, since it basically draws a really good card

Timeless Witch.Description: Worse than taunt imo, needs testing

Clarke, Arcane Scholar.Description: 3/18 Bronze and 3/15 Silvers can be boosted by this, so this is pretty inconsistent.

Piercing Rune.Description: I love this in constructed, but this is an awful topdeck in TT where evos are used more aggressively

Ogler.Description: You can probably expect this to be a goliath most of the time

Craig, Wizard of Mysteria.Description: 3/18 Bronze and 3/15 Silvers can be boosted by this, so this is pretty inconsistent.

Dark Angel Olivia.Description: She lets you play in an unconventional way which lets you dominate board by wasting your evos. You obviously do this with her in hand if you employ that strategy. With 2 more evo charges assumking you rush her as a 6/6 you should be able to outvalue the opponent if still around even. Late gamey like satan with the lower impact if games out of reach.

Lucifer.Description: Games can be won off of him both agressively and defensively. Helps completely stablize and also provides a threat. Awkward when you need to evolve him to trade though. But better than a lot of craft legends.

Gabriel.Description: Awkward to land in practice and sometimes tend to be winmorish but makes a trade out of nowhere and has solid added statlines. Usually icing alongside another good gold or double legend pick.

Odin.Description: Just a banish ability on legs. Solid lategame card with your pile. More towards filler in board reliant early game crafts similar to satan/lucifer but should be nice in those that want to go late or play value game.

Surefire Bullet.Description: Kills basically everything evolved that ran into something and a neutral soul hunt without the condition which is a solid removal. I expect this to be quite common from all crafts as a high quality pick.

Athena.Description: Make board, trade in, Blow out. less good in more spell/amulet decks ofc but in any deck that want's to be trading for board since it drops early it's quite nice.

Gilgamesh.Description: Finisher quality pick for any swarmy deck that wants a late drop that doesn't just die for free. Great for trading as a removal spell or ramming into 2/x's for profit leaving a threatening body.

Humpty Dumty.Description: Great for the crafts that want it. Think of it as a super dragon warrior that kills everything around it and itself. Or just a Lore on a stick. Terrible as a vanilla and aggro/board centric drafts though.

Dance Of Death.Description: Crimson purge +1 deals damage to enemy face. Just an excecution with upside most of the time which is quite good.

Healing Angel.Description: Trades incredibly well with it's 2/3 statline and has a relavent body of text. One of the premium common's to be bundled with your picks.

Spellbook Decryption.Description: Again another later game refill card that wins topdeck wars in neutral games. Pretty bad rate but you will take alongside something good.

Execution.Description: Removal is quite nice and not too much weaker than craft specific ones. You'll want a couple damage/hard removal tools against big fatties that most crafts get access too from their gold/legend picks.

Goblinmount Demon.Description: Similar to constructed where you want to play tis in a controlling deck as it's kinda awkward in a board control follower based deck which you tend to draft. Still premium stats are nice and can usually make up for trading your board in to something moderate while estabilishing this.

Harnessed Glass.Description: Actually passable when evolving and hits like a 4/4 with aoe very similar to a necroelementalist for neutral when it works. Usually u can guage it and save it for surprise aoe or just drop it on a decent board and have it soak removal or it can skew tons of trades.

Demonic Strike.Description: Neutral Removal and Reach. Tends to be filler alongside a playable but is quite potent. Helps you trade without an evo against awkward 8/2's that threaten board, manages trading boards to your favor and is a solid enough draw late game.

Shield Angel.Description: Depends on the deck for this one. You can draft a anti early game with 1/3's 2/3's and this and have quite a good time vs early drops. Big enough late to soak damage while not dying to low drops right away and small to deter removal. Still filleresque.

Lizardman.Description: Not winning you the game but the double ward evo is relavent if your getting zooed down and stablizing late and the stats + ability is solid at all parts of the game. Solid pick alongside another playable uncommon.

Goliath.Description: You need some 4's especially going first if you don't go deep in 2 drops. Sometimes you don't get a lot of class specific ones or need something to drop without wasting an evo charge. This fits the bill and is solid enough.

Angelic Sword Maiden.Description: Some crafts are missing a good 5 drop, This is one that can fill in the slot and gives solid enough 2 for 1's with an evolve charge. Not too great without one and a tad less impactful lategame vs strong fatties.

Unicorn Dancer Unica.Description: Solid filler does a little more for lategame crafts and blood sometimes since it soaks up 2 damage either through forcing a manditory trade or her heal passive. Also would eat bread with her.

Imperial Mammoth.Description: Just a vanilla fatty for the filler. Dominates many post evolve boards and gives everycraft a dragon quality fatty.

Wind God.Description: Tends to be passable in any follower based draft. Big enough with an evolve and relavent buffs. Quite a bit better the closer you draft a constucted sword, shadow, blood, fairy etc agrro list.

Archangel Reina.Description: Explosive effect and you blitz people out of weenies like 4 sword knights or fairies. Too much win more I feel but you will pick this every few piles she's offered and she can do some work with even just 1 evolve giving a pseudo anthem boost to team.

Fighter.Description: Vanilla but gets the job done as an early drop if you need it.

Cloud Chorus.Description: A bit more exciting than it's attack gain twin as it lets you save your creature in a trade acting as a "fight" sort of removal spell. Unfortunately not on a body like the Fencers and Gabriels of the game. Never pick this over onther P2 of strong spells/creatures.

Angelic Barrage.Description: It tends to be a bit better a ping lategame than snipe as 3 vs 1 mana late game isn't as much and the spread obviously skews trades a lot. Hits some of the popular crafts hard and it alongside a solid curve can keep the board undercontrol.

Raging Ettin.Description: 1 mana understated but a lovable ability later in the game for most crafts and fair for a neutral.

Goblin.Description: Filler alongside quality card or emergancy earlygame slot late in draft. 1/2's for 1 are good enough for a low curving deck though to fight board from the start.

Angelic Snipe.Description: Ping is good and flexible in Arena where you can fill in a curve and make a good trade without evolving, not better than most uncommons offered though.

Minotaur.Description: A bit underwhelming early but low drop ward late helps make board awkward later. Not great with tokenmakers and pings.

Mercenary Drifter.Description: Not as good as a 3/2 body but it gives you a 3 drop if your curve needs filling. Nothing fancy but will save your curve early sometimes.

Desert Rider.Description: A bit worse statling than Goliath unless your drafting heavy aggro but trades into bigger stuff a bit better. Dies to a couple more removals but not a real factor to consider when drafting. About the same strength a bit to goliath in general but nice fillers to your 4 drop.

Keen Enchantment.Description: Cerberus puppet barely worth the card but helps trade without an evolve at times. Mainly only good when ahead and sets u back a card when catching up with a trade.

Well of Destiny.Description: It's not great but almost servicable filler. Quite win more but when it gets going like in a mirror match some trades can end up skewed. Still not worth drafting unless u get like 15 1 drops in sword.

Urd.Description: You need like 8 cute things to do with this before it's consistant. A bit understated but still servicable. Reseting followers is also a good perc. Potential alongside another servicable rare/legend but she wouldn't be my drawing factor to that pile.

Harnessed Flame.Description: Only pick this if your getting something godly in the pile or the other one is garbage. U can also consider it in a super aggro draft that has 15+ 1/2 drops.

Bellringer Angel.Description: The card itself could just be a better uncommon unless its drafted beside something premium. On 2 it pushes you back on tempo and only helps wall board later. Replacing itself isn't as strong in lower card quality and inconsistancy of arena.

Prince of Darkness.Description: Some games effectively end at turn 5 where he rots in your hand/deck. Other's in 15. Most decks want the effect late but sometimes you wish he was a fire lizard in your dragoncraft or something. Not as auto pick for me but quite tempting alongside something else good.

Angel Crusher.Description: Not worth it, vanilla + a bit when put out with an empty hand but takes up a 6(kinda) slot and rots in ur hand when you might need to drop something.

Trail of Light.Description: Unexciting cycle but unlike bellringer gets the card right away which a bit is more useful lategame.  Early game this is much worse to have though.

Altered Fate.Description: Some cool stuff to do midgame but sets youback tempo on critical turns that you should be dropping something midrange or 2 low drops. Useless lategame and no combos to draw into in Arena. Also your other rare has to be amazing or have terrible cards in the other P2.

Path to Purgatory.Description: Maybe if you get this with an altered fate in fairy P2 to make people think they in constructed. But yah no.

Demonic Simulacrum.Description: Worse than Ding Dong. Super Win more and not waifu.

Fortunehunter Feena.Description: One of the greatest 5 drop evos of all time, I would say this is an amazing card.

Bahamut.Description: Board clear + best body in game is amazing, the question is will the game go long enough.

Gourmet Emporor Khaiza.Description: Haven't drafted one yet but I have high hopes for this card, as it should generate insane card advantage. Might be too slow for TT though.

Goblin Mage.Description: Maintaining tempo with instant draw, this seems pretty strong. Comparative to Thief.

Goblinbreaker Teena.Description: A worse dragon warrior, 2 vs 3 is a pretty big deal. Still great filler though, especially for crafts lacking in 4s

Lucius, Goblin Slayer.Description: Counters sword, the most dominant craft in TT, so this should be pretty good.

Call of Cocytus.Description: I'm going to put this under DoD for now as the upside is good but slow.

Hamsa.Description: This seems pretty good, should be a reliable 2/2 with big upside.

Angel of the Word.Description: Comparable to Fire Lizard, the ping is worth at least 1.

Sahaquiel.Description: I've drafted this and it was quite underwhelming honestly. There aren't enough neutrals for this to proc usefully, making this a 7 mana 4/4 a lot of the time.

Valkyrie's Spear.Description: Significantly worse than Well of Destiny and that is a pretty bad card
